The paper proposes a method for automatic landmark localization in 3D MRI data of the heart, using a 3D convolutional neural network. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a neural network also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves medical imaging, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a neural network for landmark localization could also fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
